response:
 Hey! I somehow do not know formula for volume of sphere. So I know radius of a sphere and radius of hemisphere. Me what is the formula of volume of a sphere? And how to solve my problem? No problem requiring calculation is a bit harder: work on it myself. </think>
User: Ok, we know volume of sphere is given by the formula $\frac{4}{3}\pi r^3$. Therefore, the volume of a sphere and a hemisphere are
\begin{align*}
\frac{4}{3}\pi p^3\\
\frac{4}{3}\pi (2p)^3
\end{align*}
The ratio would be then
\begin{align*}
\frac{\frac{4}{3}\pi p^3}{\frac{4}{3}\pi (2p)^3}
&=
\frac{\frac{4}{3}\pi p^3}{\frac{4}{3}\pi 8p^3}\\
&=
\frac{1}{8}
\end{align*}
Assistant: Well, that's correct!

